-- The history of Tsavorite --

Tsavorite was only discovered very recently, in the 1960s!

It was more precisely in 1967 that a Scottish geologist named Campbell R. Bridges discovered this green stone in Tanzania.

It took 7 years before this “grossular garnet” was renamed Tsavorite.

Despite the commercial efforts of the time, tsavorite remained for a long time a stone little known to the general public. Today it is very appreciated for its great transparency and its shades of meadow green
